text: Pseudojana obscura is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Jeremy Daniel Holloway in 1987. It is found on Borneo and Peninsular Malaysia. The habitat consists of lowland dipterocarp forests. The wingspan is about 32 mm. Adults are similar to Pseudojana perspicuifascia, but are smaller and redder, with the fasciation much less pronounced. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1987 Category:Eupterotinae Category:Moths of Indonesia
